Pain de campagne (Basic country loaf)

Feed starter overnight:
- 50g water
- 25g whole wheat flour
- 25g bread flour

Mix starter with water and honey in the morning:
- 100g starter
- 205g water
- 20g honey

Mix in flour, then autolyse for at least 30 min (up to 2 hours)
- 150g whole wheat flour
- 150g bread flour (preferably canadian wheat)

Add 6g salt and knead for 5 minutes then do several slap and folds to create a taught ball. 

Laminate by spreading into a thin sheet, folding in thirds, and rolling up into a tight log

Place in a baking tray for bulk fermentation, with periodic coil folds for 3 to 12 hours
depending on temperature

Lightly flour surface and tipmout onto counter. Stretch sides then fold in thirds. Stretch in
opposite direction and roll into a log. Pinch ends and seam to seal. Place upside down in a 
banneton lightly dusted with rice flour. Cover and place in fridge overnight.

Preheat dutch oven to max temp. Score bread and bake for 20 min at 230C. Remove from dutch oven and
bake an additional 10 min, rotating half way. 
